description: The Ice Truck Killer leaves Dexter a surprise at the scene of one of Dexter's recent kills, placing him firmly in the cross hairs of his own Homicide Division colleagues.
name: Return to Sender

description: J'onn Jonzz, the Martian Manhunter, comes to Earth to warn of an impending alien invasion. Part 3 of 3
name: Secret Origins: Part 3

description: The Ice Truck Killer is finally identified, but something about the suspect doesn't sit right with Dexter, who must also deal with the menacing return of Rita's paroled ex-husband.
name: Circle of Friends

deck: The first Christmas special for Doctor Who and what better way to celebrate than with an alien invasion.
name: Christmas Invasion

deck: A disfigured man approaches the team, and tells them he had been in touch with Mulder.
name: William

description: The strange suicide of a powerful woman leads Dexter to suspect her shrink of murder, but he gets a shock when a visit to the suspect opens up dark secrets from Dexter's past.
name: Shrink Wrap

deck: Doggett discovers new information regarding his son's murder.
name: Release

description: Dexter is joined by Rita, Debra and Rudy for a weekend away when he learns that his biological father - whom he was told died thirty years ago - has just recently passed away and left him everything he owned, including his house.
name: Father Knows Best

description: The Ice Truck Killer leaves Dexter the most horrifying crime scene imaginable, forcing him to confront a horrific suppressed memory from his past; Rita must hire a lawyer when her ex sues for sole custody of their children.
name: Seeing Red

deck: A man with strange mental abilities retreats into a fantasy world.
name: Sunshine Days

description: The Ice Truck Killer kidnaps someone close to Dexter, forcing him into a trap that will forever change his life, while Doakes begins to harbor suspicions about Dexter's odd behavior.
name: Truth Be Told

deck: In a special, double length episode, Mulder is brought before a tribunal and asked to defend his work to date.
name: The Truth: Parts 1 & 2

deck: The second series of Doctor Who starts here and to start off The Doctor and Rose travel to New New York on a New Earth.
name: New Earth

deck: You know you are going to have a fun time when there is Queen Victoria and Werewolfs in the same episode of Doctor Who
name: Tooth and Claw

deck: The return of Sarah Jane Smith
name: School Reunion

description: In the Season One finale, Dexter follows the clues left for him by the Ice Truck Killer in an effort to rescue his kidnapped loved one, while Rita's ex tries to convince her that Dexter is too dangerous to be around their children.
name: Born Free

description: Doctor Otto Octavius, one of Peter's childhood teachers, gets revenge on the Hardy family for cutting off the funding for his research, by kidnapping Mrs. Hardy's daughter, Felicia.
name: Doctor Octopus: Armed and Dangerous

description:
Spider-Man was seen robbing the Metropolitan Museum, while Peter Parker was home in bed. All of a sudden a supposedly new hero, Mysterio, arrives.

This episode was loosely based on The Amazing Spider-Man #13.
name: The Menace of Mysterio

description:
Sara "Pez" Pezzini is a New York City policewoman. During a shootout with a mob henchman, an ancient weapon attaches to her wrist and saves her life.

Her search for justice for a slain childhood friend and her murdered patner brings "Pez" into contact with the Witchblade, an ancient, intelligent, living weapon she is only beginning to understand.
name: Pilot

description: Jameson is becoming obsessed with destroying Spider-Man. So he hires a man named Mac Gargan to try out a new scorpion suit, made in the laboratories of Empire State University. But the mutation of the suit begins to turn Gargan into a monster.
name: The Sting of the Scorpion

description: Learning to adapt to the Witchblade, and her new partner Jake McCarty, Sara Pezzini's role in the Rialto Theater incident is questioned during a hostile meeting with the police review board. Captain Joe Siri makes a big announcement. Sara and Jake tangle with Ian Nottingham over a deranged ex-special forces soldier a "Black Dragon". Captain Bruno Dante is introduced.
name: Parallax

description:
Peter has a job interview at the Hardy Foundation Research Center. But his interviewer, Dr. Mariah Crawford, is visited by an old lover, Sergei Kravinoff aka Kraven the Hunter.

Note: Calypso appears as Dr. Mariah Crawford.
name: Kraven the Hunter

description: John Jameson, Jameson's son, finds a strange black liquid while collecting a rock called Promethium X on the moon. The black liquid finds it's way to Spider-Man, giving him a new black suit and the Kingpin sends Rhino after the Promethium X
name: The Alien Costume: Part 1
Have Yourself A Morlock Little X-Mas

description: Spider-Man is becoming attached to his new suit. But Eddie Brock has framed Spider-Man for the Promethium X robbery. Alaster and Kingpin send Shocker after Eddie to dispose of him. Now, Spidey will begin to see what the suit is really worth.
name: The Alien Costume: Part 2

description: The symbiote takes over Eddie Brock to give birth to Venom. Now, Spidey must go up against the most dangerous enemy he's ever faced. One who is stronger, more skilled, undetected by his spider-sense, and knows Spidey's true identity.
name: The Alien Costume: Part 3

description: Norman Osborn hires a psychopath, known as the Hobgoblin, to kill the Kingpin. But the Hobgoblin plans to use Osborn and Kingpin's rivalry to his own advantage.
name: The Hobgoblin: Part 1

description: The Hobgoblin takes over the Kingpin's empire. Now Osborn and the Kingpin plan to use Spider-Man to take the goblin down.
name: The Hobgoblin: Part 2

description: A secret organization, known as SHIELD, asks for Jameson's assistants in capturing a terrorist known as The Chameleon.
name: Day of the Chameleon

description:
The Tick leads Arthur on night patrol. After hours of scouring the City, they hear an alarm at a very dangerous weapons factory. They see the Forehead and some goons stealing something. The Tick and Arthur try to thwart the crime but Forehead gets away. American Maid shows up and helps the two with the goons. They find an invitation to Chairface Chippendale's birthday party and decide to team up to take down the crime lord.

The heroes don catering outfits and sneak into the party. They are quickly caught and fed to alligators. As they escape, Chairface reveals that he is going to burn his name onto the face of the moon. The heroes are too late to stop the first three letters, but do take down Chairface and his goons. American Maid ends up respecting the Tick and Arthur.
name: The Tick vs. Chairface Chippendale

description:
On their day off, the Tick and Arthur go to Dinosaur Grotto to take a tour of an excavation. Their guide, Dinosaur Neil, takes them to his tent where he displays his experiment in growing dinosaur tissue. He accidentally eats that tissue. The heroes leave and prepare a dinner for Arthur's jaded sister Dot. Dinosaur Neil grows into a dinosaur

At the dinner, the Tick watches the news chronicle the destruction Dinosaur Neil is causing downtown. He has to fight the urge to save the City and stay with Arthur and Dot. Arthur finally caves and he and the Tick ditch Dot to save the City.

Arther figures that a giant aspirin will save Dinosaur Neil. They get a big prescription and the Tick enters Dinosaur Neil's mouth to administer the medicine. After a rough battle with a tongue, the Tick hurls the pill down the throat and hops out. Dinosaur Neil regains his human form and joins the heroes at dinner with Dot.
name: The Tick vs. Dinosaur Neil

description:
The Tick and Arthur get an invitation to the Evil Eye Cafe where Mr. Mental will be performing mind tricks. He calls the Tick to the stage and hypnotizes him. He feigns releasing his hold on his mind and the Tick and Arthur go home. Mr. Mental reveals his plan to his assistant: the Tick is going to help Mr. Mental break into a facility that will guarantee that Mr. Mental's mind is the greatest in the world.

That night, Mr. Mental reenters the Tick's mind and tells him to get to the laboratory. He does so and Arthur catches on that the Tick's mind is not his own. He gathers Die Fladermaus, the Crusading Chameleon, and the Sewer Urchin to help snap Tick out of his task. They fail, but Mr. Mental's power begins to wain. He finds the Tick's worst nightmare and unleashes it - a day job in an office. With his mind weakened, the Tick goes back under Mr. Mental's control.

The Tick delivers the Thinking Cap and Mr. Mental dons it and does become mighty with his mind. Arthur notices, however, that it runs on an internal combustion engine. He gets the heroes to attack Mr. Mental and the Tick pulls the choke lever, thereby flooding Mr. Mental's mind. The Thinking Cap explodes and the City rests peacefully after another successful caper.
name: The Tick vs. Mr. Mental

description:
It is shopping day and the Tick and Arthur visit Stuart's Food Castle. While they are there, however, a bread bomb explodes. Other such incidents occur around town and the Tick heads out to investigate.

The Tick interviews the dean of the local baking school, who just happens to get a call about a bread bomb threat. The Tick finds the bread and, to stop it from destroying the school, eats it. He is successful in quelling any expansion by using a rolling pin over his body. The Breadmaster, the man behind these crimes, is not pleased.

The Breadmaster accelerates his plans by demanding mass cooking supplies while threatening to bread bomb more places in the City. The mayor gives in to these demands. The Tick determines to ambush the Breadmaster at the sugar plant. He does, but it does not end well. Fortunately, the Breadmaster drops a clue that leads the duo to the municipal swimming pool, where the Breadmaster is preparing a souffl to consume the City.

The Breadmaster is easily caught, but his self-rising souffle has already begun to expand. The Tick talks the Human Bullet into using his cannon to create a sonic boom. The noise is loud enough to erupt the souffle and the City is safe under a freshly fallen snack.
name: The Tick vs. The Breadmaster

description:
The plants in the City are inexplicably coming to life. The Tick and Arthur witness a plane crop dusting trees, which results in the trees moving. The Tick leaps aboard the plane and gets a look at El Seed, a diabolical plant bent on subjecting animals to his plant minions. El Seed spills his plant elixir on the Tick and the Tick falls to the ground. The elixir causes the trees to come alive, as well as making the Tick extremely loopy. The Civic-Minded Five arrive just in time to save the people in the park before things get out of hand, especially now that the Tick is acting odd (and growing things from his body).

The Tick visits the hospital and learns that he probably only has twelve hours until he becomes a full vegetable. Figuring that El Seed has the antidote, the Tick and Arthur look for clues as to a hideout. The find it but get waylaid by El Seed dusting a corn field with his elixir. Fortunately, the Tick can grow corn form his body so he and Arthur are able to march with the crop to El Seed's base. They muscle the antidote from El Seed, restore the Tick, and then restore the corn army. The Civic-Minded Five take El Seed into custody.
name: The Tick vs. El Seed

description: Taking a night off, the Tick and Arthur head to a night club that caters to heroes. Unfortunately, Arthur is not allowed and gets pointed to the Sidekick's Lounge. In the club, the Tick learns that he is not the only one going by his name. Barry, the club owner's bratty son, also calls himself the Tick and he is none-too-pleased at meeting the real superhero version. The two clash and Big Shot steps in to mediate. All the while, a shrimpy villain looking to make a name for himself plants bombs around the club. Fortunately, Arthur alerts the heroes and he and the real Tick save the club and catch the bad guy. The Tick also muscles the fake Tick and gets to keep the name.
name: The Tick vs. The Tick

character_credits.name: The Evil Midnight Bomber What Bombs at Midnight

first_appearance_characters.name: The Evil Midnight Bomber What Bombs at Midnight

description:
The Tick awakens one morning with a terrible cold. Arthur gets some mail for the neighbor and delivers it. Unfortunately, it was all a ruse. The neighbor is an alien, Thrakkorzorg, and intends to conquer the Earth with a cloned army of the Tick. He first clones Arthur and sends the evil clone to get a tissue sample from the Tick. He fails miserably as the Tick sleeps, as the Tick is nigh invulnerable.

The real Arthur is able to free himself and tries to stop the evil clone from getting the tissue sample. He is thwarted, however, by the Tick. The evil clone gets the sample and the two heroes are too late in stopping Thrakkorzorg from cloning the Tick. Sadly, the sample came from the Tick's snot, so the clone is mucus-based. They take the fight to the roof and the Tick has a terrible time eliminating his clone.

Arthur, meanwhile, grabs a tool from Thrakkorzorg's apartment, one that should send the alien back to his own dimension. After giving Tick the high sign, he switches in the machine. The machine opens a portal that begins sucking Thrakkorzorg into it. The Tick snorts his mucus clone and sneezes him into Thrakkorzorg and they both careen into the new dimension. This clears out the Tick's cold. Sadly, Arthur is now sick.
name: The Tick vs. The Uncommon Cold

description:
A robotic dog breaks into a laboratory and steals some machinery. Meanwhile, the Tick and Arthur are unable to microwave a pizza. They go to an electronics store and pick up the last microwave but are beset by the robotic dog. The owner, an evil genius child, needs the parts to complete his master plan. The dog gets the microwave but the Tick lassos its leg with an extension cord, thereby getting a ride. The cord falls off, however, and the Tick and Arthur end up following by taxi. The arrive in a lovely neighborhood.

The two are invited in a home where the mother and father explain that their son is a genius, albeit a tad misguided. The Tick heads out to try and talk some sense into the boy Charles. This just drives Charles to do something drastically evil, like pulling the Moon into the Earth. The parents fail at talking sense into Charles and it is the Tick who has to reverse the process. He ducks an attack by the dog and the dog crashes into the console controlling the Moon. It returns to its orbit and the secret lair falls apart. The boy may not give up evil, but his abilities to further his plans will take a while to clean up.
name: The Tick vs. Brainchild

description:
In space, a test monkey is accidentally hurled into some cosmic rays. The effects cause him to become a genius monkey. He hijacks the ship and launches himself back to earth. The U.S. government, at the suggestion of American Maid, hires the Tick and Arthur to get Yank the monkey before Pineapple Pokopo, a dictator of an island nation close to Yank's landing spot.

The Tick, Arthur, and American Maid fly out to Pokopanesia as tourists, where the dictator has already enslaved Yank. Fortunately, Pineapple Pokopo has no idea that the clearly costumed superheroes are anything more than tourists and he asks American Maid to dinner to do some market research to up the tourism on his island. Meanwhile, Yank is to build a machine to take over Hawaii, but seems to be getting dumber as he goes.

American Maid is found out and is about to be fed to Sharks when the Tick shows up to save the day. Yank informs the group that he's really built an escape pod and they all leave Pokopanesia. The U.S., unaware of Yank's reversion, makes him director of the space program.
name: The Tick vs. Pineapple Pokopo

description:
After some spring cleaning, the Tick and Arthur are visited by some peaceful Mole Men, including the king, as they vacation. The Tick takes them under his wing in order to help them have the best surface vacation ever. While out and about, the Mole King sees Mindy Moleford, a model (with a mole), and desires her to be his Mole Queen. She seems genuinely interested, but her publicist keeps thwarting the king. He even has the Mole Men arrested. Meanwhile, a Lava Man has reached the surface with the mission to kill the Mole King.

A large battle ensues and the Mole Men begin digging a trench. Mindy joins and the Tick fills the trench with water, thereby negating the Lava Man. Mindy admits that her mother was a Mole Woman and her father was a spelunker. She decides to leave the surface and joins the Mole King in his subterranean kingdom.
name: The Tick vs. The Mole-Men

description: The Tick and Arthur return to the City to find that nearly everyone is gone. The few heroes that remain (only because they couldn't get a ride out) inform them that a new menace is ravaging the City. The Tick goes toe-to-toe with the problem - a hulking clown. The clown sends the Tick into space and the rest of the heroes scatter. Only American Maid and Die Fladermaus remain to fight and that doesn't last long. They unwittingly lead the clown to the Civic-Minded Five's headquarters. They are about to be smashed until the Tick falls back to Earth (he had been on an existential journey through his mind while in space) and lands on the clown.
name: The Tick vs. The Proto-Clown

description: As a the threat of the Terror returns to the world, the Tick tries beefing up on superhero gear. He maxes out Arthur's credit card and gets kicked out of the apartment. Arthur tries to fight the Terror with American Maid but finally calls out for the Tick's help. The Tick saves the day and the two friends are reunited.
name: The Tick vs. Arthur's Bank Account

description:
While on patrol, the Tick and Arthur meet a lovely woman named Carmelita. She, too, has a moth suit and explains that her father made them and placed a code in one of them. She and Arthur strike up a romance and the Tick is left to patrol alone. But not alone! He makes a new sidekick out of wood.

While patrolling, the Tick sees Arthur and Carmelita get attacked by some Swiss guys looking for Carmelita's father's codes. The bad guys are thwarted but the friends are swallowed by a whale that happens to be running through the country. Inside the whale they find Carmelita's father, who instructs them to burn the Little Wooden Boy to smoke their way out. It works.
name: The Little Wooden Boy and the Belly of Love

description:
The Tick heads a team that is sent to the Moon to repair the damage done formerly by Chairface Chippendale. He blunders the mission terribly by mistaking a bomb for his jet-pack. While he gets blasted through space, the people of the City mourn his loss. Arthur is asked to be a sidekick for Die Fladermaus. He tries it, as well as sidekicking for other heroes, but nothing works out.

Meanwhile, in space, the Tick runs into Omnipotus, Devourer of Worlds. Omnipotus promises to take Tick back to Earth if the Tick will be a help to Omnipotus. The help includes rubbing feet and plucking eyebrow hairs. The two arrive at Earth and Omnipotus starts eating. The Tick convinces Omnipotus that the Earth is worth saving. Omnipotus only does so on account of being friends with the Tick. Omnipotus takes a bite of the Moon and then leaves.
name: Alone Together

description:
The Tick and Arthur corner two criminals: Venus and Milo. Venus nearly brings the Tick under a love spell but Arthur snaps him out of it. The bad guys run into a bathroom but their escape is thwarted by a janitor, who is mistaken for a fake crime fighter called Plunger Man.

While the Tick and Arthur work on new crime fighting techniques, Venus hatches a plan to earn her a coveted Enemy Award. She devises a way to ensnare the Tick in a love spell so that he can do her crime-spree bidding. Fortunately for her, the Tick lands in her car. He nearly succumbs to her love spell before Arthur saves him again. Milo pulls out a machine and zaps the men's arms off. Milo collects the arms and the two villains drive away, leaving the Tick and Arthur unsure of what to do.

Milo makes two robots that very poorly resemble the Tick and Arthur and leads them on a crime spree. The City buys the story and consider the heroes as outlaws. Arthur notices a trend in the crimes, however, and figures that Venus is making a killer outfit, most likely for the Enemy Awards. They head out to find the location of the award show. They are able to convince the patrons of the Evil Eye Cafe to tell them where it is.

The Tick and Arthur crash the party but their evil robot counterparts begin to pummel them. The Tick is able to convince his arms that he's been good to them and they in turn beat up their host robot. Fortunately, Plunger Man (the janitor so happens to be back to fix a toilet) is there to reattach the Tick's arms. The Tick apprehends the bad guys and clears he and Arthur's names.
name: Armless But Not Harmless

character_credits.name: The Evil Midnight Bomber What Bombs at Midnight

first_appearance_characters.name: The Evil Midnight Bomber What Bombs at Midnight

description: While out on patrol, Arthur and the Tick run into Leonardo da Vinci. He tells them that he and other notable scientists have been captured and brought to the present by a madman who wants to send a bomb back to the Renaissance to plunge the world back into the Dark Ages and then use the inventors to redo their work while taking the credit. Leonardo escapes to find help. The madman pulls some Mongolians into the present to hunt him down. The Mongols fail and the Tick leads the charge to the madman, who is now supported by a time-traveling army. The madman releases his bomb once all his lost and the Tick travels to the past to defuse it. With the past safe, the Tick and Arthur send each inventor back to their own time.
name: Leonardo da Vinci and His Fightin' Genius Time Commandos!

description:
Brainchild Charles reprograms his nanny's brain to become a rampaging tyrant in the City. She takes the Tick captive and Charles changes him into a two-headed bird in hopes of auctioning the hero to the highest bidder.

Arthur rallies some local heroes that manage to infiltrate the auction. The Tick is returned to normal and helps to take down the bad guys. The fight is ultimately broken up when Charles's parents return home.
name: Coach Fussell's Lament

description:
At a flower show, the Tick, Arthur, and American Maid visit the 400 Year Bloom. El Seed attempts to steal it, however, and Arthur is asked to protect the flower. All he has to do is play music so that the flower doesn't do its "bad bloom." Despite Arthur's best efforts, El Seed snags the 400 Year Bloom while the Tick is out on patrol.

El Seed allows the 400 Year Bloom to bloom the bad way and it gets out of control. It grows and begins to rip up the City. Despite El Seed's best efforts, he is unable to stop the heroes from singing to the plant to calm it down. The bloom is reduced to normal size and the bad guys are taken to jail.
name: Bloomsday

description:
The Tick and Arthur call in Die Fladermaus for help in picking out new furniture. A beautiful woman named Ottoman sidetracks the endeavor, however, when she makes the furniture come to life. Ottoman heists all the furniture in the City, including the most comfortable chair in the world, in order to make her Ottoman Empire. This chair is used against the Tick and he finds himself powerless to escape its comfy clutches. But, when confronted with the option of evil running loose, the Tick is able to free himself.

Die Fladermaus is conflicted throughout the battles with Ottoman. He finds that he loves her, and she loves him back. But, when he learns of her desire to marry him, Die Fladermaus wavers. This buys enough time for the Tick, Arthur, and American Maid to spring into action. A big fight goes down on a floating rug and is stopped by a jumbo jet flying by. Ottoman escapes with Die Fladermaus in tow.

Die Fladermaus manages to escape but leads Ottoman to Arthur's apartment. Thinking quick, Arthur has the Tick take the most comfortable chair in the world to the roof. There, they spring a trap that gets Ottoman to sit in it and become so relaxed so as to forget her evil ways.
name: Evil Sits Down for a Moment

description:
The Tick and Arthur are featured on the hit show "Heroes," a show similar to "Cops." While on their rounds, they meet and momentarily defeat a new villain, the Deadly Bulb. The Deadly Bulb resurfaces and kidnaps Arthur and the cameraman. Arthur is used as bait while the cameraman is to film the Deadly Bulb killing the Tick -- all so everyone will forget the fact that the Deadly Bulb has a live pig for a leg.

The Tick finds the Deadly Bulb but gets duped into becoming the world's largest filament in a large light bulb. Fortunately, American Maid gets the drop on the Deadly Bulb by throwing an apple that the pig-leg chases. The Tick is freed and the Deadly Bulb is taken into custody by the police.
name: Heroes

character_credits.name: The Evil Midnight Bomber What Bombs at Midnight

first_appearance_characters.name: The Evil Midnight Bomber What Bombs at Midnight

description: In the Season Two premiere, Dexter finds himself unable to kill again after the harrowing conclusion to the Ice Truck Killer case, and strays from his personal code with disastrous results; Debra returns to work but may not be ready.
name: It's Alive!

description:
The Tick runs from doing chores and into battle with a thief stealing the glass from windows. He confronts one of the thieves and finds that she is really a conglomeration of ants. This sends the Tick for a loop and he finds a superhero psychiatrist to help him cope.

While the Tick works out his issues with ants, Arthur teams up with American Maid and finds that all the glass is being taken to a giant anthill. They infiltrate the hill and find that all the glass is being melted down and formed into a giant magnifying glass. The ants want revenge on the humans for frying them. The superheroes do not fare well, as they are captured and placed in a people farm. Fortunately, the Tick is able to snap out of his state of fear and save the day.
name: Ants in Pants!

description:
Synopsis

A robber flees from the police as the Tick and Arthur walk home from finishing some Christmas shopping. The robber changes into a Santa suit and continues his attempt to escape from the cops. He runs headlong into the Tick. The Tick is thrilled to see Santa and allows the robber to escape. Seeing the police, the Tick seeks to intervene on "Santa's" behalf. The robber eventually slips and slides off a roof and into an electric sign; after being zapped, the robber plummets to the ground.

The Tick and Arthur host a Christmas party, but the Tick is mortified at the thought of frying Santa. The guests at the party - fellow superheroes - try to break the news to the Tick that Santa is not real. The Tick is appalled that superheroes could think such.

Nobody has checked on the robber and he dusts himself off. Five clones appear and the robber notes that the clones do as he says. This Santa army invades an electronic store and takes a large amount of goods. The army runs away and finds the Tick's party group out caroling. The Santa's attack and the Tick finds himself torn between protecting the City and protecting Santa. The Tick finds that he is unable to hit a Santa. The robber - now going by the name Multiple Santa - is hit into an electric box and more clones pop out. The clones beat on the superheroes and then raid the City even further.

Defeated, the Tick and Arthur head back to their apartment. Arthur continues to try to help the Tick realize that Santa isn't real. Inside their apartment, however, a group of secret service elves meet the duo. Santa Claus appears and applauds the Tick's continued belief and tells him to stop the rogue Santa's. He also hands out gifts like candy. Arthur is thrilled that Santa is real and pulls out a pop-gun he received as a boy. The elves see the gun as a threat and break it. Santa apologizes and replaces the gun with a pencil box set.

The Tick and Arthur head out to stop the Multiple Santa. Santa Claus tips them off that Multiple Santa has gone to the dam to use the electric current to further multiply the Santa Army. The duo heads towards the dam and sees that they are too late; Multiple Santa has already broken into the dam and received a jolt that creates a deluge of Santas. The Tick has to literally swim through the Santa's to get to Multiple Santa. A fight ensues and the Tick is confronted with, once again, having to rationalize hitting Santa. He gives a clone a noogie instead and realizes the static electricity erases the clone. The Tick begins noogie-ing the clones and starts a wave of static electricity that wipes the rest out. Multiple Santa is arrested and the Tick, as well as the rest of the City, is free to enjoy Christmas again.
name: The Tick Loves Santa!

description:
Synopsis

The Tick and Arthur are abducted by aliens. On their ship, Arthur is taken away and held captive as a spy of the Heys, an alien race determined to end the universe. The Tick, however, is treated to space cookies and an introduction to the Whats, an alien race determined on stopping the Heys. In his cell, Arthur is questioned about the Heys' plans by a huge alien and is threatened with torture. Fortunately, the Tick comments that Arthur looks a lot like the Heys and the Whats realize their mistake before anything painful happens to Arthur.

With Arthur freed, the Whats tell the duo more about the Heys. For instance, the Heys are dramatics and have not yet destroyed the universe because their leader has been giving his "Goodbye to Everything" speech for the last thirteen years. Also, the most powerful weapon of the Heys is closing in on the Whats' ship. Upon learning that the Whats power their ship with fear, the Tick has Arthur hooked up to the ship. One look at the alien torturer is enough to send the ship hurtling through space faster than it has ever gone. It is not enough, however, and the weapon - called the Infinity Ball - continues to gain on the Whats.

With no other options, the Whats decide to try some new technology and to fly at the speed of lint. (Nobody knows how lint gets in your pocket. It's that fast!) They hurtle through space at unknown speeds and lose the Infinity Ball. They find, however, the black hole that could end the universe. The Whats are sucked into the black hole and Arthur hooks himself back up to the ship to fuel it with his fear. The Whats escape and land on the Hey mothership, which conveniently has an anti-gravitational field around it.

The Tick dresses up as a Hey (again, which look like Arthur) and infiltrates their ship. He arrives just in time for the Hey leader to finish his speech and launch a devise into the black hole that will destroy the universe. The Tick lunges for the devise but comes up short. Gravity, however, elongates his body and the Tick grabs the devise and uses his will to defy physics and pull himself back into the Hey mothership. The devise is dismantled and the Tick and Arthur turn to see the Hey race staring at them in anger. The mood quickly shifts when the Infinity Ball arrives. The Tick challenges it and the ball lightly smacks the Tick in the face and then falls to the ground. The Heys immediately begin worshipping the Tick.

Back home, the Tick relates the previous night's events to his friends. Without proof, however, no one believes that he saved the universe.
name: The Tick vs. The Big Nothing

deck: Wonder Woman works to clear Steve Trevor from implications of sabotage, eventually discovering that Baroness Von Gunther is behind framing him.  She is aided by a young boy who is a fan of detective novels.
name: Wonder Woman Meets Baroness Von Gunther
The Tick vs. Dot and Neil's Wedding

description: Dexter remains on the trail of a dangerous new victim, while the traumatized Debra loses control on the job and a high-profile FBI agent arrives in Miami to investigate a newly discovered serial killer, the Bay Harbor Butcher.
name: Waiting to Exhale
